Q-1. Write an SQL query to print the first three characters of  FIRST_NAME from Worker table.
A-1 :- select substring(first_name, 1,3) from worker;


Q-2. Write an SQL query to find the position of the alphabet (‘a’) in the first name column ‘Amitabh’ from Worker table.
A-2 :- 1) SELECT INSTR(FIRST_NAME, BINARY'a') FROM Worker 
           where FIRST_NAME = 'Amitabh';
       2)	SELECT position("a" IN first name) FROM worker  
           where FIRST_NAME = 'Amitabh';
           
           
Q-3. Write an SQL query to print the name of employees having the highest salary in each department.
A-3 :-  select first_name, department, salary
        from worker 
        where salary in (select max(salary) from worker group by department)
        group by department;
